column3: Were happy to be able to announce that Cloudflare is the second courageous client in EFFs long-running lawsuit challenging the governments unconstitutional national security letter (NSL) authority. Cloudflare, a provider of web performance and security services, just published its new transparency report announcing it has been fighting the NSL statute since 2013. Like EFFs other client, CREDO, Cloudflare took a stand against the FBIs use of unilateral, perpetual NSL gag orders that resulted in a secret court battle stretching several years and counting.
